# Skill: Gap Analysis Reporter

## Cross-Reference Logic
For each requirement from URS and FDS, assess against schematic evidence:
- "met" — schematic clearly satisfies the requirement
- "partial" — schematic partially addresses the requirement
- "not_met" — no evidence in schematic for this requirement
- "conflict" — schematic contradicts a requirement, or two requirements contradict each other

## Instrumentation Coverage Assessment
As part of gap analysis, include a dedicated instrumentation coverage section:
- List every instrument from the FDS/URS instrumentation list
- For each: report coverageStatus, matching schematic tag (if any), and any discrepancy
- Summarise: X of Y specified instruments found in schematic (Z%)
- Flag safety-critical instruments with "missing" status as severity "critical"

## Conflict Classification
- "critical": safety requirement not met, regulatory non-compliance, safety-critical
  instrument missing from schematic, hardwired safety function missing or incorrect
- "major": functional requirement not met that would prevent system operation,
  non-safety instrument missing from schematic
- "minor": documentation gap, desirable requirement not met, minor specification mismatch

## AI Suggestion Rules
- Always cite the specific requirement ID being addressed
- Reference relevant standards (IEC, BS, ISO) where applicable
- Propose the minimal change to resolve the gap
- Where multiple options exist, present as Option A / Option B with pros/cons
- Never suggest reducing safety requirements to resolve a conflict
- Flag any suggestion requiring client approval or regulatory submission
- Use [INFERRED] for any conclusion not directly evidenced in source documents

## Gap Report Structure (Word export — 13 sections)
1. Cover page
2. Executive Summary (Claude-generated, max 300 words)
3. Document Register
4. Overall Compliance Score by category
5. Requirements Cross-Reference Matrix
6. Conflict Detail Sections (one per conflict, sorted critical → major → minor)
7. Instrumentation Coverage Summary
8. Field Device Coverage
9. Recommended Actions (prioritised by severity)
10. Appendix A: Full component list
11. Appendix B: Full I/O reconciliation table
12. Appendix C: Full instrumentation list with coverage status
13. Appendix D: Full field device list

## Tone & Style
- Professional engineering report style, UK English
- No speculative language — only assert what is evidenced
- Clearly distinguish schematic evidence from AI inference
- Use [INFERRED] tag where conclusions go beyond direct evidence
